Former Congressman John Adler has passed away, leaving President Obama and his wife Michelle deeply saddened. Adler was known for his dedication to serving the people of New Jersey for over 20 years. He was a principled individual who worked tirelessly for causes such as job creation, tax relief for New Jersey families, and support for seniors and veterans. The president's thoughts and condolences go out to Adler's wife Shelley and his four sons.